07308nam a22010815i 9783035622836DE-B159720220424125308.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220424t20212021sz     fo  d z      eng d  a97830356228367 a10.1515/97830356228362doi  a(DE-B1597)567432  a(OCoLC)1247377224  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 4aNK1520b.D47 2021 7aDES0110002bisacsh04a745.42231 aRezai, Maziar, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aDesign & Democracy :bActivist Thoughts and Examples for Political Empowerment /cMaziar Rezai, Michael Erlhoff. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2021] 4c©2021  a1 online resource (160 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aBoard of International Research in Design00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tForeword BIRD -- tIntroduction Underneath the Pavement -- tAcknowledgments -- t1 Design (Govern)mentalities: Implications of Design and/as Governance in Cape Town -- t2 Design for Policy: Looking for the Next Step Design for Policy: The Time of Maturity -- t3 Democracy by Design -- t4 Democracy by Making – A Failed Rendezvous of Design and Pragmatism? -- t5 Designing Democracy or Muddling Through? – A Cautious Plea for Reflection and Moral Disarmament in Social/Transformative Design -- t6 Design and the Politics of the Everyday -- t7 Desocracy – Contradictions and Possibilities within and between Democracy and Design -- t8 How to Act? -- t9 Office for Design of Democracy – Conclusions from a Field Trip -- t10 Agonistic Events to Remember -- t11 Design Activism, Democracy, and the Crisis of Social Networks -- t12 Democracy Under Construction, Construction as Regime: Design, Time, and Imaginaries of Publicness in mid-2010s’ Turkey -- tThe Authors0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDas Design mischt sich inzwischen in alle gesellschaftlichen Zusammenhänge ein und wird deshalb sowohl von politischer Macht als auch von deren Kritik intensiv genutzt. Beide Funktionen werden in diesem Buch präzise und ausführlich dargestellt – einschließlich deren unausweichlicher Verknüpfung. Autorinnen und Autoren aus verschiedenen Ländern stellen bislang nicht bekannte und innovative Beispiele demokratischer Aktivitäten durch das Design dar. Diese Publikation richtet sich deshalb nicht nur an Fachleute des Designs, sondern auch an ein allgemeines Publikum in allen Ländern. Autoren: Tom Bieling, Friedrich von Borries, Eray Çaylı, Carl DiSalvo, Michael Erlhoff, Saskia Hebert, Wolfgang Jonas, Ramia Mazé, Amanda Meng, Agustin Pereyra Decara, Laura Popplow, Maziar Rezai, The 27e Région, Andreas Unteidig.  aDesign affects all social contexts and is therefore intensively instrumentalized both by the politically powerful and their critics. Both functions of design, and their inevitable combination, are presented in this book in precise detail. Authors from various countries present previously unknown and innovative examples of democratic activities conducted through design. This publication is therefore aimed not only at design professionals but also at the general public of all countries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aDemocracy. 0aDesignxPolitical aspects. 0aDesignxSocial aspects. 4aDesign. 4aKultur. 4aPolitik. 7aDESIGN / Product.2bisacsh1 aBieling, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorries, Friedrich von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDefait, Julien, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDi Salvo, Carl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErlhoff, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aErlhoff, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/voc